This project can be build using the ant build tool.

The following targets are available:
 - jar:			creates chordsharp4j.jar, chordsharp4j-lib.jar and chordsharp4j-examples.jar
 - doc:			generates the API-docs (public entities only) in ./doc
 - devel-doc:	generates the API-docs (public and private) in ./doc-devel
 - dist:		generates archives containing the sources, the jars and the documentation:
 				DistributedLogger.zip, DistributedLogger.tar.gz, DistributedLogger.tar.bz2
 - clean:		removes all generated files
 - test:		runs unit tests

For more information regarding the implementation of the Chord# Java Interface
have a look into the API-docs. The general structure is described in the
documentation of the package "de.zib.chordsharp".

./src	contains the application's sources
./test	contains the sources of the junit test cases
